cs.FL, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the randomness of formal languages, which is a topic closely related to formal language theory (cs.FL). The use of automatic martingales involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and probability theory (cs.PR). The paper also discusses the dependence of randomness on the text, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the nonrandomness of automatic families of languages, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
